kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
Clouds floating above the surface</i>

26
00:01:17,321 --> 00:01:22,160
<i>I am open from midnight to seven of the morning after.
kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
Clouds floating above the surface</i>

27
00:01:22,970 --> 00:01:23,915
<i>People call this...</i>

28
00:01:24,045 --> 00:01:26,557
<i>Midnight Restaurant.</i>

29
00:01:27,060 --> 00:01:28,476
<i>How is business doing?!</i>

30
00:01:29,242 --> 00:01:31,471
<i>Well enough, I'd say.</i>

31
00:01:31,734 --> 00:01:34,654
~ SHINYA SHOKUDO ~
Midnight Restaurant

32
00:01:34,654 --> 00:01:40,246
Episode 5
Butter Rice

33
00:01:45,155 --> 00:01:46,812
Ahh... Right!

34
00:01:46,837 --> 00:01:49,358
Yuriko is getting married!

35
00:01:49,503 --> 00:01:52,063
It's with her first love from
middle school or something,

36
00:01:52,231 --> 00:01:54,815
and they got in touch again because
of business, completely by chance!

37
00:01:54,859 --> 00:01:56,362
Wait a second...

38
00:01:56,551 --> 00:01:58,020
How old is Yuriko again?

39
00:01:58,136 --> 00:01:59,191
36.

40
00:01:59,233 --> 00:02:00,511
Arafo*.
(*Around 40)

41
00:02:00,567 --> 00:02:03,034
So that means... what...

42
00:02:03,591 --> 00:02:06,870
A reunion after twenty years?!

43
00:02:06,895 --> 00:02:08,313
Sure does!

44
00:02:08,457 --> 00:02:11,032
Fantasy!!

45
00:02:11,557 --> 00:02:14,373
Compared to her, we're just...

46
00:02:14,398 --> 00:02:16,506
"We" what?
Don't group us all with you?

47
00:02:16,728 --> 00:02:19,457
I knew it.
It does exist!

48
00:02:19,549 --> 00:02:20,949
Is it fate?

49
00:02:21,223 --> 00:02:23,317
That red thread...

50
00:02:23,342 --> 00:02:26,931
The only red thread you bring
to mind is a tangled one.

51
00:02:27,451 --> 00:02:30,471
Still better to have a tangled
one than nothing at all!

52
00:02:30,504 --> 00:02:31,550
Guess so?!

53
00:02:31,631 --> 00:02:34,484
But take a closer look, and
you'll start seeing the flaws already.

54
00:02:34,668 --> 00:02:36,530
Enough with that.

55
00:02:47,365 --> 00:02:48,650
Been a while.

56
00:02:48,675 --> 00:02:49,788
Ohh!

57
00:02:51,637 --> 00:02:56,346
Ohh... Looks promising.

58
00:02:57,673 --> 00:02:59,970
Back when I was studying
in Paris and penniless,

59
00:03:00,212 --> 00:03:04,517
I would often spend
time at bistros like this.

60
00:03:05,813 --> 00:03:07,282
Here, should we sit over there?

61
00:03:07,395 --> 00:03:09,145
All right.

62
00:03:09,297 --> 00:03:11,570
I think I saw him on TV.

63
00:03:14,109 --> 00:03:18,787
<i>Be it 3 stars or 5, this place
has very little to do with that game.</i>

64
00:03:19,314 --> 00:03:21,623
Master.
For starters, some beers.

65
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:23,556
<i>(*a thicker variety of aburaage,
deep-fried tofu)</i>
Also... You have some atsuage* left?

66
00:03:23,581 --> 00:03:24,388
Sure do.

67
00:03:24,578 --> 00:03:26,402
<i>- Then, we'll have that.
- Still, Komi-chan...</i>

68
00:03:26,427 --> 00:03:30,769
<i>brought along exactly the kind of
species I detest, food critics.</i>

69
00:03:35,584 --> 00:03:37,720
Tasty.

70
00:03:40,153 --> 00:03:43,614
Haven't had a beer in Japan in
quite some time, all right.

71
00:03:43,807 --> 00:03:46,416
Had grown tired of wine,
so all the better.

72
00:03:46,453 --> 00:03:47,835
Ahh... I'm glad I
brought you here, then.

73
00:03:47,860 --> 00:03:52,546
<i>(*veal sweetbreads,
renowned gourmet delicacy)</i>
But that ris de veau* earlier
today was just a tragedy.

74
00:03:52,571 --> 00:03:55,137
A little more and I would
have puked right there.

75
00:03:55,218 --> 00:03:56,463
Is that so?

76
00:03:56,531 --> 00:03:58,883
The sauce's flavor
was barely masking it,

77
00:03:59,141 --> 00:04:02,135
but they didn't even wash
away the blood properly.

78
00:04:02,238 --> 00:04:07,352
It's scary to see such amateurs be
allowed to serve food and be praised for it.

79
00:04:07,793 --> 00:04:11,771
In Paris, they'd have
gone belly-up by now.

80
00:04:20,136 --> 00:04:22,759
But, tell me.
You like caviar?

81
00:04:22,784 --> 00:04:24,000
Well, I have no particular...

82
00:04:24,235 --> 00:04:27,097
Next time, I'll take you to
this restaurant I often go to,

83
00:04:27,122 --> 00:04:29,556
<i>(*Traditional Russian pancakes)</i>
and have you try blin*.

84
00:04:29,853 --> 00:04:33,752
It's the best dish you can get,
among those using caviar.

85
00:04:35,694 --> 00:04:39,335
Instead, get me a
fine bottle of champagne.

86
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:47,513
Someone is stinking up
my ochazuke, all of a sudden.

87
00:04:48,404 --> 00:04:51,147
Here you go, atsuage is ready.

88
00:04:52,101 --> 00:04:53,746
Ohh!

89
00:04:54,343 --> 00:04:56,363
Thank you.

90
00:05:00,812 --> 00:05:03,916
But, how about that
pizza from your last show...

91
00:05:03,990 --> 00:05:06,160
- Italian?
- Yeah.

92
00:05:06,309 --> 00:05:09,476
Ahh... That pizza...

93
00:05:09,507 --> 00:05:12,035
was second rate
even by Tokyo standards.

94
00:05:12,123 --> 00:05:18,108
Right when he was about to
completely kill the atmosphere...

95
00:05:21,350 --> 00:05:22,806
Come on in!

96
00:05:23,116 --> 00:05:25,330
How are you?

97
00:05:26,319 --> 00:05:29,856
Goro-san is one of the very
few remaining of a dying breed,

98
00:05:29,881 --> 00:05:32,082
the street singer.

99
00:05:46,761 --> 00:05:47,632
Here you are.

100
00:05:47,657 --> 00:05:50,808
Butter rice and a
small serving of Tonjiru.

101
00:05:53,098 --> 00:05:55,985
I'm always thankful.

102
00:06:11,992 --> 00:06:14,564
<i>Waiting about thirty
seconds for the butter to melt...</i>

103
00:06:14,589 --> 00:06:17,601
<i>is Goro'san style.</i>

104
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:31,352
Just a little...

105
00:06:31,844 --> 00:06:33,562
A little...

106
00:06:37,876 --> 00:06:42,556
<i>And after that, adding a touch
of soy sauce, and stirring gently.</i>

107
00:06:51,967 --> 00:06:54,071
Excuse me.
Can I have that as well?

108
00:06:54,282 --> 00:06:55,568
Me, too.

109
00:06:55,971 --> 00:06:57,408
Coming.

110
00:06:58,055 --> 00:06:59,522
What now...

111
00:06:59,653 --> 00:07:03,553
Don't! You already had
two servings of ochazuke.

112
00:07:05,313 --> 00:07:08,085
I take no money from Goro-san.

113
00:07:08,143 --> 00:07:09,446
And instead of that...

114
00:07:09,553 --> 00:07:13,082
<i>he graces me with just one song.</i>

115
00:07:13,110 --> 00:07:15,203
<i>Always the same one.</i>

116
00:07:23,783 --> 00:07:27,416
"Wandering about the last 40 years,"

117
00:07:27,748 --> 00:07:31,474
"I am known around these parts
for even making crying kids smile,"

118
00:07:31,499 --> 00:07:34,014
"Goro is my name."

119
00:07:35,814 --> 00:07:40,634
Ahh... If you were in the middle
of a meal, just go ahead and eat.

120
00:07:45,814 --> 00:07:54,048
"It was a long and winding
road to Hakodate."

121
00:07:54,162 --> 00:08:01,630
"Past the storming waves I went."

122
00:08:01,845 --> 00:08:10,296
"As you sent me away, you hid
the tears flowing down your face."

123
00:08:10,417 --> 00:08:16,950
"Memories of you ache
like a distant wound,"

124
00:08:17,261 --> 00:08:26,604
"a desire hard to control."

125
00:08:32,795 --> 00:08:38,923
"Waves of pain sweltering my soul."

126
00:08:43,441 --> 00:08:45,392
Thanks for that.

127
00:08:51,945 --> 00:08:54,124
Have you heard that?!
That was great!

128
00:08:54,149 --> 00:08:56,654
So poignant.

129
00:08:57,061 --> 00:08:58,869
Butter rice.

130
00:09:01,845 --> 00:09:04,669
One serving of
butter rice for me as well.

131
00:09:07,024 --> 00:09:08,854
Coming.

132
00:09:23,989 --> 00:09:29,649
<i>(*French for frying pan
**creamed meat+breadcrumbs)</i>
Here is wagyu poele* on a
bed of red wine sauce and quenelles**.

133
00:09:54,165 --> 00:09:55,247
Sensei?!

134
00:09:55,496 --> 00:09:56,866
Ohh...

135
00:09:59,035 --> 00:10:00,435
The ingredients are quite passable.

136
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:05,958
<i>(*black hair)</i>
Yes, we get A5 class kuroge*
wagyu delivered to us daily.

137
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:10,090
It is so fresh and delicate,
it could even be eaten raw.

138
00:10:11,430 --> 00:10:13,928
The quenelle is made with
three different kinds of pesto,

139
00:10:13,953 --> 00:10:16,327
while the sauce was
infused with truffles, and...

140
00:10:16,352 --> 00:10:17,372
If you'll excuse us,

141
00:10:17,747 --> 00:10:20,435
<i>(*upscale Shibuya district)</i>
Sensei's participation is
required at a party in Hiroo*.

142
00:10:20,460 --> 00:10:22,378
Here...

143
00:10:24,864 --> 00:10:26,584
Shall we get going?

144
00:10:26,609 --> 00:10:27,949
Yes.

145
00:10:33,456 --> 00:10:34,656
<i>Master.</i>

146
00:10:34,705 --> 00:10:36,765
<i>I upset you yesterday, didn't I?</i>

147
00:10:36,790 --> 00:10:40,670
For bringing a famous food critic
like Toyama Masao here...

148
00:10:40,790 --> 00:10:42,390
I guess.

149
00:10:42,566 --> 00:10:45,006
I just wanted to show him...

150
00:10:45,423 --> 00:10:47,803
What real food tasted like.

151
00:10:49,626 --> 00:10:51,196
Butter rice.

152
00:10:51,998 --> 00:10:53,775
To make something like butter rice,

153
00:10:53,873 --> 00:10:58,033
all you need to do is adding butter on
top, so you can make it at home.

154
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:01,690
My wife has spent so long overseas,

155
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:04,820
all she gives me is bread.

156
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:07,206
Ohh Ohh!

157
00:11:57,559 --> 00:11:59,349
Will that...

158
00:11:59,617 --> 00:12:01,967
street singer come tonight?

159
00:12:02,953 --> 00:12:04,983
Goro-san, you mean?

160
00:12:05,597 --> 00:12:09,867
He comes only once
per week, on Thursdays.

161
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:16,320
That street singer thing,
can he make a living out of that?

162
00:12:17,130 --> 00:12:19,270
Don't ask me.

163
00:12:31,048 --> 00:12:33,609
So... Here you go.

164
00:12:33,832 --> 00:12:37,782
Sadly I don't have enough
change for that.

165
00:12:37,860 --> 00:12:40,680
Ohh... I'll come again anyway,

166
00:12:40,819 --> 00:12:43,209
so you can give it to me next time.

167
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:05,940
Can you drop me over there?

168
00:13:06,023 --> 00:13:07,753
But we're still far from your place?!

169
00:13:08,114 --> 00:13:09,293
It's all right.

170
00:13:09,318 --> 00:13:12,085
There is a place
I need to drop by to.

171
00:13:12,110 --> 00:13:13,720
You can go ahead.

172
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:17,020
Ahh... Fine.

173
00:13:19,699 --> 00:13:21,559
From there on in,

174
00:13:21,656 --> 00:13:25,146
Toyama-san would come
by every Thursday night.

175
00:13:35,289 --> 00:13:36,857
How's things?

176
00:13:37,264 --> 00:13:38,392
Ahh.... Sensei!

177
00:13:38,417 --> 00:13:41,025
That sushi place you
reviewed was really something.

178
00:13:41,374 --> 00:13:42,942
The chief was happy with it as well.

179
00:13:42,967 --> 00:13:46,098
I'm so envious!
I'd love to go there.

180
00:13:47,509 --> 00:13:51,639
I guess with my salary it
would be a little over the top?

181
00:13:54,693 --> 00:13:57,433
Master.
Butter rice.

182
00:13:58,567 --> 00:14:00,037
Coming.

183
00:14:00,561 --> 00:14:01,401
What shall we have?

184
00:14:01,426 --> 00:14:04,475
Our Critic Sensei
comes all the time now,

185
00:14:04,630 --> 00:14:07,993
but Goro-san has been nowhere
to be seen for quite some time.

186
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:13,170
Goro-san!

187
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:14,530
Is it all right?

188
00:14:14,670 --> 00:14:15,620
Yes.

189
00:14:15,710 --> 00:14:17,260
Sorry for pushing you so much.

190
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:22,419
But low-paying jobs are
gaining steam in this bad economy.

191
00:14:24,093 --> 00:14:26,043
I'll leave you to it.

192
00:14:47,573 --> 00:14:49,639
The day Goro-san finally showed up...

193
00:14:49,839 --> 00:14:54,639
was about three months after
Toyama-san had become a regular.

194
00:15:02,743 --> 00:15:04,833
Goro-san...

195
00:15:08,583 --> 00:15:11,293
I owe you so much for all this time,

196
00:15:11,825 --> 00:15:14,074
but now my career
as street singer is over.

197
00:15:14,453 --> 00:15:16,803
Is anything wrong?

198
00:15:17,559 --> 00:15:20,519
Can't play guitar anymore.

199
00:15:21,255 --> 00:15:25,155
Broke my fingers doing factory work.

200
00:15:25,449 --> 00:15:29,075
I'm going around thanking all the
people who kindly offered me their patronage.

201
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:31,330
That's so sudden...

202
00:15:32,209 --> 00:15:33,889
So long.

203
00:15:34,345 --> 00:15:36,485
Goro-san.

204
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:39,547
By any chance,
do you remember me?

205
00:15:41,511 --> 00:15:45,551
I'm Ritsuko's little brother, Masao.

206
00:15:45,803 --> 00:15:49,293
You know, the one
you gave guitar lessons to...

207
00:15:49,502 --> 00:15:51,252
Your index goes here.

208
00:15:51,423 --> 00:15:53,256
While the middle finger goes here.

209
00:15:53,281 --> 00:15:55,430
Press hard with the ring finger here.

210
00:15:55,455 --> 00:15:56,834
Here you go.

211
00:15:57,359 --> 00:15:59,441
- Bon apetit!
- Yes.

212
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:02,240
I'm sorry I
only had this much.

213
00:16:03,672 --> 00:16:07,432
Masao, do it this way,
and it'll taste even better.

214
00:16:07,665 --> 00:16:09,415
Just a little...

215
00:16:11,229 --> 00:16:12,939
A little here...

216
00:16:16,303 --> 00:16:17,963
That's right!
So tasty.

217
00:16:19,426 --> 00:16:21,320
"That's right!
So tasty!"

218
00:16:21,667 --> 00:16:22,957
Stop that!

219
00:16:28,741 --> 00:16:31,046
Is that so?

220
00:16:32,123 --> 00:16:35,043
How about any family?

221
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:38,830
No, I have none.

222
00:16:40,123 --> 00:16:42,783
My sister is alone as well, now.

223
00:16:44,439 --> 00:16:46,925
But, Ritsuko...

224
00:16:46,950 --> 00:16:52,615
She was going to marry
whom her parents chose,

225
00:16:53,959 --> 00:16:59,041
but she changed
her mind and came back.

226
00:17:03,813 --> 00:17:10,790
But, when she did, you
had already left Hakodate.

227
00:17:23,472 --> 00:17:26,305
A lot has happened since then,

228
00:17:26,740 --> 00:17:30,960
but she's still living by herself.

229
00:17:31,986 --> 00:17:37,339
She runs a small karaoke
bar in Matzukaze-cho.

230
00:17:38,910 --> 00:17:45,013
I am sure she's
still waiting for you.

231
00:17:50,913 --> 00:17:52,513
But...

232
00:17:52,930 --> 00:17:55,220
It's already too late, now.

233
00:17:56,899 --> 00:18:00,579
Butter rice never loses
its taste, no matter what.

234
00:18:07,136 --> 00:18:08,986
Here you go.

235
00:18:12,648 --> 00:18:15,312
Goro-san.

236
00:18:15,337 --> 00:18:20,717
So there really was someone
in Hakodate, as you sang.

237
00:19:17,839 --> 00:19:19,909
Just a little...

238
00:20:31,813 --> 00:20:34,023
<i>According to Toyama-san,</i>

239
00:20:34,813 --> 00:20:38,513
<i>Goro-san returned
to Hakodate after that,</i>

240
00:20:39,140 --> 00:20:43,080
<i>and seems like he's
helping out his sister at her bar.</i>

241
00:20:49,021 --> 00:20:50,941
What is this?

242
00:20:50,966 --> 00:20:53,766
It's all right, go ahead and eat.

243
00:20:54,150 --> 00:20:55,830
Yes...

244
00:20:59,846 --> 00:21:01,692
After Goro-san left,

245
00:21:02,029 --> 00:21:06,413
less and less people ordered butter rice.

246
00:21:07,472 --> 00:21:11,868
But, at least as far as this man goes,
there was no change.

247
00:21:17,473 --> 00:21:19,573
Great!

248
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:23,400
Master!

249
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:25,510
Butter rice for three!

250
00:21:25,756 --> 00:21:27,208
Uh?!

251
00:21:27,233 --> 00:21:29,203
Coming.

252
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:32,241
Sensei.

253
00:21:32,451 --> 00:21:35,311
Are you reviewing this place for
some magazine or something?

254
00:21:35,416 --> 00:21:37,198
Won't write a thing!

255
00:21:37,426 --> 00:21:40,096
I don't want people
to know about this place.

256
00:21:40,136 --> 00:21:42,196
Why is that?

257
00:21:42,405 --> 00:21:45,620
If customers start piling up,
I won't be able to come.

258
00:21:45,645 --> 00:21:48,761
- Not to mention...
- Not to mention?

259
00:21:48,786 --> 00:21:52,546
You can't rate this kind of food.

260
00:21:56,343 --> 00:21:57,933
Another one!

261
00:22:01,895 --> 00:22:03,245
Still,

262
00:22:03,270 --> 00:22:07,340
can there truly
be a food critic like that?

263
00:22:07,696 --> 00:22:09,086
Coming.

264
00:22:11,175 --> 00:22:15,560
~ to be continued ~

265
00:22:16,798 --> 00:22:19,891
As simple to make as it is tasty,

266
00:22:19,916 --> 00:22:22,702
butter rice consists in adding
butter on top of your rice,

267
00:22:22,727 --> 00:22:24,517
and waiting for it
to melt, nothing more.

268
00:22:25,843 --> 00:22:28,256
The flavor of butter
is just irresistible.

269
00:22:28,745 --> 00:22:33,753
Also, as butter sold
in stores already has salt,

270
00:22:34,093 --> 00:22:38,857
only add a touch,
just a touch of soy sauce.

271
00:22:40,071 --> 00:22:41,612
Excess salt, intake warning!

272
00:22:41,637 --> 00:22:46,365
More than that, it's enough not
to ruin that irresistible flavor.

273
00:22:46,549 --> 00:22:49,229
<i>(*seaweed)</i>
You can eat it wrapped in nori*,

274
00:22:49,379 --> 00:22:52,309
or any other spice is fine as well.

275
00:22:53,408 --> 00:22:55,330
Ohh?! Goro-san,
you were here?

276
00:22:55,355 --> 00:23:01,055
Nice dreams to you....

277
00:23:01,463 --> 00:23:09,249
Good night, everyone!

